original_result.completion_text:
Q4: What happens if I leave before receiving my RSUs?\nA: You will receive any unvested shares that have been earned up until the time of departure. Any vested shares remaining after your departure will vest according to the terms specified in your original award agreement.\n',
'instruction': 'Summarize the key points regarding how new hires are awarded RSU grants and their vesting schedule.'}
 New hires are awarded RSU grants which are then converted into a monetary value based on the 9-month average exchange rate and the average closing stock price over 21 working days ending with the last day of the month they start employment. For example, given a €200,000 grant target and an average stock price of $177.91, resulting in approximately 1,300 RSUs being granted. These RSUs become visible in Schwab accounts two weeks post-grant and are subject to specific vesting schedules. Unvested shares upon departure are paid out while vested shares follow the original award agreement terms.

